Persona's **Asset Editor** opens when you **double-click** an animation asset in the **Asset Browser**. For more information about the **Asset Browser**, see [](Engine/Animation/Persona\AssetBrowser).

You can use the **Asset Editor** to add Notifies, including Particle Systems, Sound Cues, and Animation Notifies, to specific points in time on the tracks of animation assets.

![](AssetEditor.png)

To add a Notify to an animation track, **right-click** the track, click **Add Notify**, and do one of the following:
* To add a new Particle System, click **PlayParticleEffect**.
* To add a new Sound Cue, click **PlaySound**.
* To add a new custom Animation Notify, click **New Notify**, and give your new Animation Notify a name.

![](AssetEditor_AddNotify.png)

For more information about Animation Notifies, see [](Engine/Animation/Sequences\Notifies).

